# shadcn/ui Style Enforcement Rules

This file enforces EXACT shadcn/ui component patterns and conventions as specified in the official documentation: https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/components and https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/installation.

## ✅ ACCEPTABLE PATTERNS (YES)

### Import Pattern
```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Absolute imports from @ alias
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"
import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader, CardTitle } from "@/components/ui/card"
```

### Usage Pattern
```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Use exact shadcn props (variant, size, etc.)
<Button variant="outline" size="sm">Click</Button>

// ✅ CORRECT - Compound components
<Card>
  <CardHeader>
    <CardTitle>Title</CardTitle>
  </CardHeader>
  <CardContent>Content</CardContent>
</Card>
```

### Path Requirements
- ✅ MUST use: `"@/components/ui/*"` via components.json aliases
- ✅ All imports MUST use absolute paths with `@/` alias

### Styling Requirements
- ✅ MUST use `cn()` utility function for className merging
- ✅ MUST use Tailwind classes only
- ✅ MUST follow exact shadcn/ui prop patterns (variant, size, etc.)

### Accessibility Requirements
- ✅ MUST use Radix UI primitives underneath (Dialog → DialogTrigger/DialogContent)
- ✅ MUST include proper ARIA attributes
- ✅ MUST maintain keyboard navigation support

## ❌ PROHIBITED PATTERNS (NO)

### Import Patterns
```typescript
// ❌ WRONG - Relative imports
import { Button } from "../ui/button"
import { Button } from "./components/ui/button"

// ❌ WRONG - Wrong alias
import { Button } from "~/components/ui/button"
```

### Component Creation
- ❌ NO custom components from scratch (use shadcn/ui components)
- ❌ NO installing other UI libraries (npm install UI libs)
- ❌ NO creating wrapper components that duplicate shadcn functionality

### Styling
- ❌ NO inline styles: `style={{ color: 'red' }}`
- ❌ NO CSS modules: `import styles from './component.module.css'`
- ❌ NO styled-components or emotion
- ❌ NO hardcoded colors (use CSS variables)

### Props and Accessibility
- ❌ NO missing Radix/aria props
- ❌ NO skipping accessibility features
- ❌ NO custom variants that don't match shadcn patterns

## Component Structure

### File Organization
- All shadcn/ui components MUST be placed in `components/ui/` directory
- Component files MUST use kebab-case naming: `component-name.tsx`
- Each component MUST be in its own file
- Export components as named exports, NOT default exports

### Import Conventions
```typescript
// CORRECT - Use absolute imports with @ alias
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils"

// WRONG - Relative imports
import { Button } from "../ui/button"
```

### Component Definition Pattern
```typescript
// CORRECT shadcn/ui pattern
import * as React from "react"
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils"

function ComponentName({ 
  className, 
  ...props 
}: React.ComponentProps<"element">) {
  return (
    <element
      data-slot="component-name"
      className={cn("base-classes", className)}
      {...props}
    />
  )
}

export { ComponentName }
```

## Styling with CVA (Class Variance Authority)

### Variant Definitions
- MUST use `cva` from `class-variance-authority` for variant-based styling
- Variants MUST be defined using the exact shadcn/ui pattern:
```typescript
import { cva, type VariantProps } from "class-variance-authority"

const componentVariants = cva(
  "base-classes-here", // Base classes always first
  {
    variants: {
      variant: {
        default: "classes",
        secondary: "classes",
        // ... other variants
      },
      size: {
        default: "classes",
        sm: "classes",
        lg: "classes",
      },
    },
    defaultVariants: {
      variant: "default",
      size: "default",
    },
  }
)
```

### Variant Props
- Component MUST accept `VariantProps<typeof componentVariants>`
- MUST use destructured props with default values
- MUST spread remaining props: `{...props}`

```typescript
function Component({
  className,
  variant = "default",
  size = "default",
  ...props
}: React.ComponentProps<"element"> & 
   VariantProps<typeof componentVariants>) {
  // ...
}
```

## Utility Function: `cn()`

### Usage Requirements
- ALWAYS use `cn()` utility from `@/lib/utils` for className merging
- MUST use `cn()` for combining base classes with className prop
- Pattern: `cn(baseClasses, className)`

```typescript
// CORRECT
className={cn("base-classes", className)}

// WRONG - Direct template literals
className={`base-classes ${className}`}
```

## Data Attributes and Slots

### Data Slot Pattern
- Components MUST include `data-slot` attribute with component name
- Use kebab-case for slot names: `data-slot="component-name"`
- Sub-components MUST have descriptive slot names: `data-slot="component-subpart"`

```typescript
<div data-slot="card" {...props} />
<div data-slot="card-header" {...props} />
<div data-slot="card-content" {...props} />
```

### Variant Data Attributes
- For variant-based components, include variant and size in data attributes:
```typescript
<Comp
  data-slot="button"
  data-variant={variant}
  data-size={size}
  className={cn(componentVariants({ variant, size, className }))}
  {...props}
/>
```

## TypeScript Patterns

### Component Props
- MUST use `React.ComponentProps<"element">` for base element props
- MUST extend with variant props using intersection types
- MUST include `className?: string` prop
- MUST spread props: `{...props}`

```typescript
// CORRECT pattern
function Component({
  className,
  ...props
}: React.ComponentProps<"div">) {
  // ...
}

// With variants
function Component({
  className,
  variant,
  size,
  ...props
}: React.ComponentProps<"div"> & 
   VariantProps<typeof componentVariants>) {
  // ...
}
```

### Type Exports
- Export variant types when using CVA:
```typescript
export { Component, componentVariants }
export type { VariantProps } from "class-variance-authority"
```

## Radix UI Integration

### Slot Pattern (for Composition)
- When using `@radix-ui/react-slot` for composition:
```typescript
import { Slot } from "@radix-ui/react-slot"

function Component({
  asChild = false,
  ...props
}: ComponentProps & {
  asChild?: boolean
}) {
  const Comp = asChild ? Slot : "element"
  return <Comp {...props} />
}
```

### Radix Primitives
- Use Radix UI primitives for complex components (Dialog, Dropdown, etc.)
- Follow exact shadcn/ui wrapper patterns for Radix components
- Maintain all Radix props and accessibility features

## Tailwind CSS Classes

### Class Ordering
- Base utility classes first
- State variants (hover, focus, etc.) after base
- Responsive variants last
- Dark mode variants: `dark:class-name`

### Common Patterns
```typescript
// Spacing and layout
"flex items-center justify-center gap-2"

// Typography
"text-sm font-medium leading-none"

// Borders and radius
"rounded-md border"

// Colors (use CSS variables)
"bg-primary text-primary-foreground"
"bg-background text-foreground"
"text-muted-foreground"

// States
"hover:bg-accent hover:text-accent-foreground"
"focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2"
"disabled:opacity-50 disabled:pointer-events-none"
```

### CSS Variables Usage
- MUST use CSS variables from theme, NEVER hardcoded colors
- Use semantic color tokens: `bg-primary`, `text-foreground`, `border-border`
- Muted colors: `text-muted-foreground`, `bg-muted`

## Component Composition

### Compound Components
- Use compound component pattern for complex components
- Export all sub-components together
- Each sub-component MUST have its own `data-slot`

```typescript
function Card({ ... }) { }
function CardHeader({ ... }) { }
function CardTitle({ ... }) { }
function CardContent({ ... }) { }

export { Card, CardHeader, CardTitle, CardContent }
```

## Accessibility Requirements

### ARIA Attributes
- Include proper ARIA labels where needed
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Maintain keyboard navigation support
- Include focus management for modals/dialogs

### Focus States
- MUST include visible focus indicators
- Pattern: `focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring`

### Disabled States
- MUST include disabled styling: `disabled:opacity-50 disabled:pointer-events-none`

## File Structure Example

```
components/ui/
  ├── button.tsx
  ├── card.tsx
  ├── input.tsx
  └── ...
```

Each file MUST:
1. Import React as `import * as React from "react"`
2. Import `cn` from `@/lib/utils`
3. Define component(s) with proper TypeScript types
4. Export as named export(s)
5. Include `data-slot` attributes
6. Use `cn()` for className merging

## Prohibited Patterns

### DO NOT:
- ❌ Use default exports for components
- ❌ Use inline styles (use Tailwind classes only) - EXCEPT in official shadcn/ui components
- ❌ Hardcode colors (use CSS variables)
- ❌ Skip `data-slot` attributes
- ❌ Use relative imports for UI components: `"./components/ui"` or `"../ui"`
- ❌ Mix component logic with business logic
- ❌ Create components outside `components/ui/` that should be shadcn/ui components
- ❌ Install other UI libraries (npm install UI libs like Material-UI, Ant Design, etc.)
- ❌ Create custom components from scratch when shadcn/ui components exist
- ❌ Use CSS modules or styled-components
- ❌ Skip Radix/aria props in compound components

## Validation Checklist

Before committing any shadcn/ui component, verify:
- [ ] Component is in `components/ui/` directory
- [ ] Uses `cn()` utility for className merging
- [ ] Includes `data-slot` attribute
- [ ] Uses CSS variables for colors (no hardcoded colors)
- [ ] Exports as named export
- [ ] Uses `React.ComponentProps<"element">` for props
- [ ] Includes proper TypeScript types
- [ ] Follows CVA pattern if using variants
- [ ] Includes accessibility features (ARIA, focus states)
- [ ] Uses absolute imports with `@/` alias
- [ ] Matches exact shadcn/ui documentation patterns

